      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;pageinfo pageinfo-primary&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;Starting with CSM 1.12, all deployments will need to use images from &lt;a href=&#34;https://quay.io/organization/dell&#34;&gt;quay.io&lt;/a&gt; . Please note that from CSM 1.14 (May 2025), upgrading will fail if it attempts to use images from &lt;a href=&#34;https://hub.docker.com/r/dellemc/&#34;&gt;Docker Hub&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;As of Container Storage Modules v1.15, Authorization v1.x will not be supported. Please migrate to Authorization v2.0 using the following &lt;a href=&#34;https://dell.github.io/csm-docs/docs/concepts/authorization/migration-guide-from-v1-to-v2/&#34;&gt;guide&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This section outlines the upgrade steps for Container Storage Modules (CSM) for Authorization.  The upgrade of CSM for Authorization RPM is handled in 2 parts:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
